  "prompt": "Do MBA grads working in Corporate Offices and watching Game of Thrones associate themselves with Boltons or Lannisters and not with Starks?",
  "response": "While MBA grads working in corporate offices might find some aspects of both House Bolton and House Lannister relatable due to the political maneuvering and strategic thinking often seen in the corporate world, it's overly simplistic to categorically associate them with these fictional families and not House Stark.\n\nThe Boltons are characterized by ruthlessness and brutality, which are not traits typically admired or aspired to in a professional setting. Meanwhile, the Lannisters are known for their wealth, strategic cunning, and political influence, which might resonate more with MBA grads due to the importance of networking, financial acumen, and strategic planning in corporate environments.\n\nOn the other hand, House Stark is known for loyalty, honor, and steadfastness \u2014 qualities that are also highly valued in corporate culture. Many MBA grads might identify with the Starks for their integrity and leadership qualities.\n\nUltimately, the choice of which Game of Thrones house resonates most with an individual would depend on their personal values and experiences. Corporate professionals might appreciate different aspects of all three houses for various reasons.",
